- She's here to get Jill.
Me and Jill had an argument.

168
00:14:10,820 --> 00:14:13,618
杰克，你快点掉头
Jack, I gotta get back to town.
Move this thing, will ya?

169
00:14:13,690 --> 00:14:16,454
在他们到派对前赶回去，行吗？
See if you can get back to the town hall
before they get there, okay?

170
00:14:16,526 --> 00:14:21,190
没问题　拿着这个
- Piece of cake.
- Take this joint.

171
00:14:28,838 --> 00:14:30,772
莉莲
Lillian?

172
00:14:30,840 --> 00:14:33,741

Lillian.

173
00:14:33,810 --> 00:14:36,870
吉尔呢？
Where's Jill?

174
00:14:36,946 --> 00:14:39,540
我和吉尔有点误会
Me and Jill,
we had a little spat.

175
00:14:39,616 --> 00:14:42,449
她比较害怕陌生的孩子
She kind of felt left out
from not knowing the new kids.

176
00:14:42,519 --> 00:14:45,352
她在哪里？她在车吗？
Where is she? Is she
in the truck with your friends?

177
00:14:45,421 --> 00:14:50,222
不，她说在里面等你
No. She told me she wanted
to wait for you inside.

178
00:14:51,528 --> 00:14:55,191
那你就和朋友出去喝酒了
While you went for
a few beers with your friends.

179
00:14:57,000 --> 00:15:00,231
那车上的人是海迪.罗杰斯吗？
That Hettie Rogers in there
with what's-his-name?

180

00:15:00,303 --> 00:15:02,237
是他
Yeah.

181
00:15:02,305 --> 00:15:05,934
天，那小女孩可长大了，对吗？
Boy, she's grown up
a little, hasn't she?

182
00:15:06,009 --> 00:15:08,000
你能别太见外吗
Jesus, lay off, will ya?

183
00:15:08,077 --> 00:15:12,605
你是赢了，但能否给个机会给我
You've won this round,
so just lay off, for chrissake.

184
00:15:12,682 --> 00:15:17,813
你别开玩笑了　这么久你还是老样子
You amaze me.
Year after year in the same old ways.

185
00:15:22,058 --> 00:15:24,083
小子　别碰她
Horner, leave her be.

186
00:15:24,160 --> 00:15:27,220
她和你没有什么关系了
It's got nothing to do with you,
so just act like a chauffeur.

187
00:15:27,297 --> 00:15:30,164
你知道吗？韦德　我们不要吵了
- You got it?
- Wade, nobody wants any trouble.

188
00:15:30,233 --> 00:15:32,258
听我说，我不想她回去
Listen to me.
I don't want her to go.

189
00:15:32,335 --> 00:15:35,930
别傻了，这可没有什么大赢家
Please don't make a scene.
Nobody is trying to win any round.

190
00:15:36,005 --> 00:15:38,064
别恶化这事了
Don't make this any worse.

191
00:15:38,141 --> 00:15:40,666
恶化它的是你。　我？
- I'm not making it any worse. You are!
- Me?

192
00:15:40,743 --> 00:15:43,234
我和吉尔本来可以好好生活的
Me and Jill,
we could've worked this out.

193
00:15:43,313 --> 00:15:46,043
这都是很正常，这是父女间的事
- It's normal.
It's a father-daughter thing.
- She called me.

194
00:15:46,115 --> 00:15:49,915
我知道她给你打电话了，你这又算那般
I know she called you.
How do you think this makes me look?

195
00:15:49,953 --> 00:15:54,151
这小孩可是无辜的，让她留下。我不会答应你这么做的
- Coming up here and treating her
like some tragic victim.
- I'm not gonna do this.

196
00:15:54,190 --> 00:15:56,852
你干什么，该死的
Just wait till
we're through, goddamn it!

197
00:16:02,665 --> 00:16:04,860
别说话
Don't say a word.

198
00:16:08,071 --> 00:16:10,266
我可没动他
I didn't hit him.

199
00:16:15,411 --> 00:16:18,073
我不会打任何人
I'm not gonna hit anybody.

200
00:16:49,412 --> 00:16:52,939
新帽子啊
New hat!

201
00:16:53,016 --> 00:16:56,713
不是，我看到吉尔在上面　对，她呆了一会
- Jill's up, I see.
- Yeah, for a while.

202
00:16:56,786 --> 00:17:01,280
她怎么了？她很好
- How's she doing?
- She's okay. She's fine.

203
00:17:01,357 --> 00:17:05,123
你们俩明天要如果需要其他人帮忙的话找我吧　好的
You two want to do anything, need
a third party, give me a call. I'm off.

204
00:17:05,194 --> 00:17:08,254
明天是猎鹿节的第一天　
Like hell you are. Tomorrow's
the first day of deer-huntin' season.

205
00:17:08,331 --> 00:17:11,994
我要你明天早点到　自己保重　韦德
I'll need you at least in the mornin'.
Take care, Wade.

206
00:17:12,068 --> 00:17:15,526
好了，也差不多了
Well, I guess that's that.

207
00:17:15,605 --> 00:17:17,937
你可得小心那些小鬼
You be careful
of that little bastard.

208
00:17:18,007 --> 00:17:22,740
他们会躲进你的裤子里　你别这样吓唬我好吗
- He's dyin' to get in your pants.
- Come on. Give me a break.

209
00:17:23,813 --> 00:17:26,043
明天见　好的
- I'll see you tomorrow.
- Okay.

210
00:17:35,425 --> 00:17:38,588
明天见　乔丹　嗯
- Tomorrow, Gordon.
- Hmm.

211
00:17:38,661 --> 00:17:42,688
今晚就会下雪了
Watch the snow.
It's coming down tonight.

212
00:17:54,210 --> 00:17:58,078
这种天气最适合捕杀坏蛋吗？
This weather
any advantage in tracking the bastards?

213
00:17:58,147 --> 00:18:00,707
别担心，汤比利先生　我知道鹿的脾性
Don't worry, Mr. Twombley,
I know where those suckers are.

214
00:18:00,783 --> 00:18:03,843
就像现在，那片丛林里鹿就少
Right about now, the does
are holding up in the brush piles.

215
00:18:03,920 --> 00:18:06,582
鹿总爱躲在那里的
The bucks are
right behind the does.

216
00:18:06,656 --> 00:18:08,624
我们也到那去
We're right behind the bucks.

217
00:18:08,691 --> 00:18:12,092
十点前就会找到鹿的
That gun gets fired before 10:00.

218
00:18:12,161 --> 00:18:16,063
不管它射不射得中猎物　我都会给一个机会施展身手
Whether it kills a deer or not,
more or less up to you.

219
00:18:16,132 --> 00:18:20,228
大约离鹿三十到三十五码
I'll put you inside 30, 35 yards of
a buck first four hours of the season.

220
00:18:20,303 --> 00:18:24,171
要不可不敢收你的钱　是吧
- That's what you're
paying me for, ain't it?
- Damn straight.

221
00:18:24,240 --> 00:18:28,267
心直口快啊　对步枪有研究吗
Done much shootin'
with that rifle yet?

222
00:18:28,344 --> 00:18:32,906
我告诉你，如果在十点能找到一只鹿的话
I'll tell you what, kid.
You get me close to a big buck
by 10:00 in the mornin',

223
00:18:32,982 --> 00:18:35,507
我多给一百块小费
there's an extra $100 in it.

224
00:18:36,686 --> 00:18:40,019
如果你捉住它的话？是的
- If you get it?
- Yeah.

225
00:18:40,089 --> 00:18:42,489
可能你不会杀它的，你认为呢？
- You might not kill it.
- You think so?

226
00:18:42,558 --> 00:18:46,324
你可能会打伤它　然后被其他人捡到
You might gut-shoot it. Cripple it
for somebody else to find and tag.

227
00:18:46,395 --> 00:18:50,661
不能保证不会发生这样的事情　特别是拿着新的枪
Can't guarantee that won't happen,
especially with a new gun.

228
00:18:51,834 --> 00:18:54,166
我也打它一枪吧
I may have to shoot it.

229
00:18:54,237 --> 00:18:57,968
我们还是各顾各的吧
- You take care of your end,
I'll take care of mine.
- Mm-hmm.

230
00:18:58,040 --> 00:19:00,008
你明白我说的吗
You understand what I'm sayin'?

231
00:19:00,076 --> 00:19:04,376
我要的是死鹿　不是还会跑那种　我明白了
- I want a deer, a dead one.
Not a cripple.
- I get it.

232
00:19:04,447 --> 00:19:08,508
不用费多大功夫你就可以打到鹿了　然后你还有时间喝咖啡
No sweat. You'll get yourself
a deer, dead, by coffee time.

233
00:19:08,584 --> 00:19:12,714
那你会有一百块小费了　太好了
- And you'll get your extra $100.
- Wonderful.

234
00:19:18,895 --> 00:19:22,228
早上好　杰森　早
- Good morning, Jason.
- Good morning, Miss Brooks.

235
00:19:23,633 --> 00:19:25,897
早上好
Morning.

236
00:19:28,604 --> 00:19:30,697

Hi, Melanie.

237
00:19:33,743 --> 00:19:36,234
韦德　吉尔呢
Wade? Where's Jill?

238
00:19:36,312 --> 00:19:38,906
我还以为她今天来上学的
I thought she was coming
to school today.

239
00:19:40,650 --> 00:19:43,778
爸爸别担心，我爱你
Don't worry, Dad. I love you. I do!

240
00:19:43,853 --> 00:19:47,016
但我明天还是不想来这里上学
But I don't want to go
to school here tomorrow.

241
00:19:58,734 --> 00:20:02,966
老兄时间到了　我们要走了
For Pete's sake, Whitehouse,
we ain't got all day!

242
00:20:13,316 --> 00:20:17,446
你没事吧　韦德
Are you okay, Wade? What was wrong?

243
00:20:17,520 --> 00:20:20,546
你干嘛呀　发什么呆
Why were you holding everyone up?

244
00:20:20,623 --> 00:20:23,786
你看到那坐宝马的家伙吗　他一定是杀了人要跑路了
Did you see that son of a bitch in that
B.M.W? He could've killed somebody.

245
00:20:23,860 --> 00:20:25,794
你有他的号码吗？我知道他是谁
- Did you get his number?
- Yeah, I know who it is.

246
00:20:25,862 --> 00:20:27,830
那就好，梅尔.乔丹
- Good.
- Mel Gordon.

247
00:20:27,897 --> 00:20:32,630
他从波士顿来的　是汤比利的侄子　他们要去阿加威湖
He's from Boston.
He's Evan Twombley's son-in-law.
They're headed to Lake Agaway.

248
00:20:32,702 --> 00:20:36,798
那老家伙和杰克去打鹿去了　我找他们麻烦去
The old man's out hunting with Jack.
I'm gonna spoil his weekend.

249
00:20:36,873 --> 00:20:39,273
别，韦德
Now, Wade...

250
00:20:39,342 --> 00:20:42,505
上了安全扣了吗？嗯
- Safety on?
- Mm-hmm.

251
00:20:49,685 --> 00:20:52,017
我没事
I'm all right.

252
00:20:53,289 --> 00:20:56,281
跟着我　我们穿过那片树林
Stay with me.
We'll cross into the next meadow.

253
00:20:56,359 --> 00:20:59,021
我以前见过你
I've seen you before.

254
00:20:59,095 --> 00:21:01,757
我以前踢球的　是吗？
- I used to play ball.
- Yeah?

255
00:21:01,831 --> 00:21:05,528
在红袜队中作清道夫　你在红袜队啊？
- Drafted by the Red Sox.
- You played for the Sox?

256
00:21:05,601 --> 00:21:08,968
在新不列颠打双Ａ后卫
- Double-A. New Britain.
- Oh.

257
00:21:09,038 --> 00:21:13,634
投手自从卡尔顿.菲克斯之后　最佳球员都是来自新汉普郡
Pitcher. Best ballplayer to come out
of New Hampshire since Carlton Fisk.

258
00:21:13,709 --> 00:21:16,837
真的？他们是这么说的
- Really?
- They said.

259
00:21:16,913 --> 00:21:22,010
我只是不太走运
Only difference between me
and that Clemens on TV is shit luck.

260
00:21:24,220 --> 00:21:27,246
上子弹没？上了
- Safety on?
- Yeah.

261
00:21:27,323 --> 00:21:30,781
就在前面　太阳出来了
- Just ahead.
- Sun's gettin' high.

262
00:21:32,495 --> 00:21:34,554
鹿长有耳朵的
Deers have ears too, you know.

263
00:21:34,630 --> 00:21:36,996
对哦
Oh, yeah.

264
00:22:12,034 --> 00:22:16,334
这很简单，他们要么清理拖车或者它被拖走了
It's simple.
Either they clean up the trailer
or it gets hauled out.

265
00:22:16,405 --> 00:22:18,339
这简直是混帐
It looks like a piece of shit.

266
00:22:18,407 --> 00:22:20,739
对　那就叫山脉风景吧
That's right.
It's called mountain view.

267
00:22:20,810 --> 00:22:23,301
但现在都不像样了
Looks like shit view right now.

268
00:22:23,379 --> 00:22:26,143
告诉他们如果不搬的话　我就去帮他搬
Tell them if they don't move it,
I'll come out and have it moved.

269
00:22:26,215 --> 00:22:28,149
走了　迟些再打给你
I gotta go. I'll call you later.

270
00:22:33,356 --> 00:22:36,154
我说过会下雪的
Told you the snow was coming down.

271
00:22:36,225 --> 00:22:39,160
拿铲子去吧
Take the grader.

272
00:22:39,228 --> 00:22:42,425
犁呢？吉米拿了
- Where's the plow?
- Jimmy took it.

273
00:22:42,498 --> 00:22:44,659

Jack's out hunting
with Evan Twombley.

274
00:22:44,734 --> 00:22:48,033
杰克和汤比利去打猎了　他的侄子早上差点干掉我了　
- His son-in-law damn near
killed me this morning.
- Huh?

275
00:22:48,104 --> 00:22:52,234
在学校门口开快车真是不要命了　我要教训他
At the school crossing. Could've hurt
some kids. I'm gonna bust his ass!

276
00:22:52,308 --> 00:22:54,833
别在这装样子
Don't go playing policeman.

277
00:22:54,910 --> 00:22:58,209
那我是什么　保安吗
What the hell am I?
A security guard?

278
00:22:58,280 --> 00:23:01,647
你雇用我　你的朋友可没有啊
I mean, you hired me.
You and your selectmen friends.

279
00:23:01,717 --> 00:23:05,380
你不想挣外块吗
You don't want
the extra police pay?

280
00:23:05,454 --> 00:23:08,218
我可没那样说过
I'm not sayin' that!

281
00:23:11,827 --> 00:23:14,295
拿着雪铲到图比那去吧
Take the grader.
Go out 29 past Toby's.

282
00:23:14,363 --> 00:23:16,991
别叫莉莲来了　她不属于这里
Don't let Lillian get to you.
She didn't belong here.

283
00:23:17,066 --> 00:23:19,091
这也是她离开的原因　尼玛
- That's why she left.
- Fuck you.

284
00:23:19,168 --> 00:23:22,069
这也是我喜欢小镇的原因
That's what I love
about a small town.

285
00:23:22,138 --> 00:23:24,834
你对每个人都很了解
ou know everybody.

286
00:23:32,648 --> 00:23:34,912
近了
Stay close.

287
00:23:37,953 --> 00:23:39,887
新脚印
Fresh tracks.

288
00:23:42,091 --> 00:23:44,924
鹿粪　可是头大鹿
Deer shit. Big one.

289
00:23:44,994 --> 00:23:47,292
汤比处先生　你的鹿
Here's your buck,
Mr. Twombley.

290
00:23:47,363 --> 00:23:49,524
我下去看一下
I'll go down and circle around.

291
00:23:49,598 --> 00:23:54,695
为了那一百块　你得辛苦一下了
You only got a little while
if you wanna collect that extra $100.

292
00:25:32,168 --> 00:25:35,103
嘿　怎么样了？
Hey. How's it goin'?

293
00:25:35,171 --> 00:25:38,106
好冷啊　你说呢
Cold. How do you think?

294
00:25:38,174 --> 00:25:41,166
说点事给我听
Yeah, sorry about that.
Tell me something.

295
00:25:41,243 --> 00:25:45,179
为什么你总在下雪天来这里喝酒
Why is it every year come first snow
you always get stuck with that grader?

296
00:25:45,247 --> 00:25:47,374
因为我要看着学校的十字路口
School. Traffic crossing.

297
00:25:47,449 --> 00:25:51,078
然后你会怎么干，挖井吗？
- So what are we doing after?
Digging wells?
- Yeah.

298
00:25:51,153 --> 00:25:53,986
别干嘛太快　好吗
Don't work too fast, all right?

299
00:25:54,056 --> 00:25:56,217
事情总有它的发展规律的
Business being the way it is,

300
00:25:56,292 --> 00:25:59,625
乔丹也老是在找借口来骂我
Gordon's looking for any reason
to lay me off earlier than usual.

301
00:25:59,695 --> 00:26:01,822
这人可是太富有了
That border jumper's got too much money
as it is.

302
00:26:01,897 --> 00:26:05,230
我告诉你那就是怀豪斯
I'll tell you who's a pisser.
Glen Whitehouse.

303
00:26:05,301 --> 00:26:07,235
他也很平凡
He was mean normal.

304
00:26:07,303 --> 00:26:11,103
但一喝酒就发疯了
But when he drank,
it was like he burst on fire.

305
00:26:11,173 --> 00:26:15,735
加拿大人都爱喝烈酒的
Brown's Canadian.
Always drank B.C.

306
00:26:15,811 --> 00:26:19,577
有次圣诞节　他忘了有一堆木头在外面
One Christmas, there was this cord
of wood out back he'd forgotten about.

307
00:26:19,648 --> 00:26:22,742
他决定叫他的孩子去拿
He decides he's gonna have
his boys stack it.

308
00:26:22,818 --> 00:26:27,050
都已经放了两个月了　木头都结冰了
Except it's been out back
for two months. The wood's all iced in.

309
00:26:27,122 --> 00:26:31,183
但他却把两个儿子都叫出去　而自己在喝酒
He grabs the boys, throws them outside.
And he's drunk.

310
00:26:31,260 --> 00:26:34,627
来　搬开它
Oh! Come on, move it.

311
00:26:34,697 --> 00:26:37,825
多美的雪光
Daylight in the swamp.

312
00:26:37,900 --> 00:26:42,530
爸　孩子们在等，鲁夫
- Pop, the kids are waiting for us.
- Rolfe.

313
00:26:42,605 --> 00:26:46,541
这可是在平时学到的东西
A lesson in work
and its rewards.

314
00:26:46,609 --> 00:26:50,340
你们总有一天会感谢我的　来吧
You'll thank me for this one day, boys.
Now, come on.

315
00:26:56,318 --> 00:26:58,411
孩子　快挖
Here we are, boys. Dig in.

316
00:26:58,487 --> 00:27:00,648
快　在这挖你们看到吗
Come on, let's do it right over here.
See that?

317
00:27:00,723 --> 00:27:03,453
快，快挖
Goddamn it!
Let's do it!

318
00:27:03,525 --> 00:27:05,652
使点力出来
Show a little muscle there.
Come on.

319
00:27:07,963 --> 00:27:12,127

There! There we go.

320
00:27:12,201 --> 00:27:14,135
好样的
Attaboy. Come on!

321
00:27:14,203 --> 00:27:16,831
爸爸，我们回去吧
Please, Pop, let's go back.

322
00:27:18,240 --> 00:27:20,174
你要作懦夫吗
What the hell are you,
a quitter?

323
00:27:20,242 --> 00:27:22,472
做懦夫吗
Huh? Get in there!

324
00:27:22,544 --> 00:27:25,069

Quitter? Huh? Huh?

325
00:27:25,147 --> 00:27:28,310
接着发生什么事了　他打我了
- So what happened?
- Oh, beats me.

326
00:27:28,384 --> 00:27:32,081
但这可能问韦德就清楚了
That's all I heard.
Wade would know more about it. Wade?

327
00:27:32,154 --> 00:27:36,523
韦德　我们在聊你爸说的：你要做懦夫吗？
We were just talkin' about your old man.
"What are you, a quitter?"

328
00:27:40,095 --> 00:27:45,294
天啊　你还有很多重要的事情做　比坐在这里讲故事好得多
Jesus, LaCoy, you got nothing better
to do than tell stories?

329
00:27:45,367 --> 00:27:49,565
遗憾的是　某天有大学生听到这事的话
The pity is, someday
some college student will come in here
and believe this shit...

330
00:27:49,638 --> 00:27:53,301
他们全把你的事写成书的
'cause you're the only one
dumb enough to talk to him.

331
00:28:12,027 --> 00:28:15,155
这就是工作
That was some job.

332
00:28:15,230 --> 00:28:19,667
我保证　我们会做的
We'll work at it, we promise.

333
00:28:19,735 --> 00:28:22,397
我知道了　你只知道喝酒
- I think I made a point.
- You just need a drink.

334
00:28:22,471 --> 00:28:24,735
韦德　你刚说什么
What was that, Wade?

335
00:28:24,807 --> 00:28:28,208
你说什么？
You say something?

336
00:28:28,277 --> 00:28:31,735
你再说一次　说啊
You got something to say, say it.
Say it!

337
00:28:31,814 --> 00:28:33,839
你这混小子
You no good pup!

338
00:28:33,916 --> 00:28:35,816
妈
Mom!

339
00:28:38,987 --> 00:28:41,683
嗯　妈
- Well?
- Mom!

340
00:28:42,958 --> 00:28:45,222
..
Mom!

341
00:28:47,029 --> 00:28:49,054
..
Mom! Mom!

342
00:29:03,579 --> 00:29:06,013
别看右边
Don't look right.

343
00:29:06,081 --> 00:29:08,777
那招牌
The sign.

344
00:29:08,851 --> 00:29:12,150
好像是拼错了字母　没有啊
Looks like it's spelled wrong
or somethin'.

345
00:29:12,221 --> 00:29:16,885
韦德　你这种人可以让这城市振兴繁荣吗
Ahh. Wade, Wade. It's people like you
who keep this town from prospering.

346
00:29:16,959 --> 00:29:19,519
我没觉得有什么不妥　我是为你好　这好多的城镇　
I'm not finding fault. It's good
for you. It's good for the town.

347
00:29:19,595 --> 00:29:22,063
这是不错的主意　对
- It's a good idea.
- Yeah.

348
00:29:22,131 --> 00:29:25,828
你在干嘛　那些人是雇来搞建设的
What did you do? Hire one of
those hippie craftsman from Concord?

349
00:29:25,901 --> 00:29:27,835
你可找到了有用之村
Think you're gettin'
something you can use,

350
00:29:27,903 --> 00:29:30,371
这可是工作的艺术
only it turns out to be
a work of art?

351
00:29:30,439 --> 00:29:35,035
无论谁在这里想进步　你都阻拦人家
Whatever somebody does to improve things
around here, you gotta find fault.

352
00:29:35,110 --> 00:29:37,203
得了
- Is that it?
- Come on.

353
00:29:37,279 --> 00:29:41,477
我只是说你的招牌有错误
I'm only sayin' there's something wrong
with "Homemade Cooking."

354
00:29:41,550 --> 00:29:45,008
招牌很好，谁说不好
The sign's fine.
What it says is wrong.

355
00:29:45,087 --> 00:29:47,681
谁要　来这里的可都是熟客
Who needs it? Everybody that
comes here, been coming here for years.

356
00:29:47,756 --> 00:29:50,122
为什么要看那招牌
What do we need a sign for?

357
00:29:50,192 --> 00:29:52,251
但我觉得这比以前更好
But I guess it's better
than what was there before.

358
00:29:52,327 --> 00:29:57,458
这以前怎么了　没什么
- What was there before?
- Nothin'.

359
00:29:57,533 --> 00:30:00,468
这以前什么也没有
There was nothin' here before.

360
00:30:00,536 --> 00:30:02,470

Hmm.

361
00:30:04,106 --> 00:30:06,631
你还好吧　嗯
- You okay?
- Yeah, yeah.

362
00:30:08,177 --> 00:30:11,010
对我以前说的话抱歉
I'm sorry about what I said.

363
00:30:11,079 --> 00:30:16,381
你说了什么　就那个你和吉尔需要第三者的事
- What'd you say?
- About you and Jill
and needing a third person.

364
00:30:16,452 --> 00:30:19,250
她回到莉莲那里吗？嗯
- She went back with Lillian?
- Yeah.

365
00:30:19,321 --> 00:30:22,518
对不起　算了吧
- Yeah. Forget it.
- I'm sorry.

366
00:30:23,759 --> 00:30:27,126
我会开始新的生活的
I'm gonna start me
one of those custody suits.

367
00:30:27,196 --> 00:30:29,756
我不会再自暴自弃了　不要这样说
- I don't give a fucking shit anymore!
- You don't mean that.

368
00:30:29,832 --> 00:30:33,859
我会的　你在找借口安慰我
- Yeah, I do.
- No, you don't. You're just pissed.

369
00:30:33,936 --> 00:30:38,498
该冷静几天　然后和莉莲谈一下
You just oughta cool off for a few days,
then have a long talk with Lillian.

370
00:30:38,574 --> 00:30:41,202
把我的感受都告诉她
Work it out with her.
Tell her how you feel.

371
00:30:41,276 --> 00:30:43,904
莉莲的心肠很软的　她不会的
- Lillian's not out to get you.
- The hell she isn't!

372
00:30:43,979 --> 00:30:47,608
莉莲自从我认识她那天就没对我好过
Lillian's been trying to nail me
to a cross since the day I met her.

373
00:30:47,683 --> 00:30:52,677
我得找个律师处理一下离婚的事
I'm gonna get me a lawyer from Concord,
and get this divorce thing rearranged.

374
00:30:52,754 --> 00:30:56,383
玛格　这鬼女人
- Marge?
- That goddamn woman.

375
00:30:56,458 --> 00:31:00,019
她想这样来打击我　我可不会放在心上的
She thinks she can cart Jill off
and leave me alone like this.

376
00:31:00,095 --> 00:31:02,859

I'm a whole lot more than pissed.

377
00:31:02,931 --> 00:31:05,764
我可活了半辈子了　深知这一切的虚幻
I've been there plenty in my life,
and I know the difference.

378
00:31:05,834 --> 00:31:07,927
这可有大区别
And this is different.

379
00:31:08,003 --> 00:31:10,335
玛格　现在需要你了
Marge, you got orders.

380
00:31:11,540 --> 00:31:14,202
打电话给我
Call me.

381
00:31:14,276 --> 00:31:18,474
今晚我去找你　好的
- Tonight. Let's get together tonight.
- Okay.

382
00:31:22,718 --> 00:31:26,176
见到杰克了？没有，他和人家今天早上去打猎了
- Talked to Jack?
- Nah. Not since last night.
He took a guy hunting.

383
00:31:26,255 --> 00:31:29,452
那人自己打伤自己了　
The fucker shot himself. Ker-bang!
That's what it sounded like.

384
00:31:29,525 --> 00:31:31,550
毫无目的的打中了自己　这可能是意外
Not on purpose.
I assume accidental.

385
00:31:31,627 --> 00:31:33,618
谁？杰克　不　另外一个人
- Who? Jack?
- The other guy.

386
00:31:33,695 --> 00:31:35,822
你怎么知道的　是对讲机说的
- How'd you hear this?
- C.B., a little while ago.

387
00:31:35,898 --> 00:31:39,163
是杰克用对讲机求救的
One of the boys comin' in. Jack on
the C.B. Callin' for state troopers.

388
00:31:39,234 --> 00:31:41,498
我还以为你早知道了
I figured you'd know
what really happened.

389
00:31:41,570 --> 00:31:44,767
我整个上午都是在铲雪　汤比利就是那个来度假的有钱人
I was on the grader. Twombley,
summer people from Massachusetts.

390
00:31:44,840 --> 00:31:48,276
乔丹的朋友　是乔丹叫杰克去陪他的
Friend of Gordon's. It was Gordon's idea
for Jack to take him hunting.

391
00:31:48,343 --> 00:31:50,834
噢　我得去看一下
Oh, boy. I gotta go.

392
00:31:50,913 --> 00:31:55,145
我要你再做一遍　我不满意这句
I want you to work on
a new logo for that. I don't like that.

393
00:31:55,217 --> 00:31:59,119
好的　在这里建一座山
- All righty.
- Put an idea of a mountain down there.

394
00:31:59,187 --> 00:32:01,678
又可以挡住狂风
Something like that
with a stream below.

395
00:32:01,757 --> 00:32:04,624
有什么事？打猎那边出事了　杰克和汤比利那边
- What's the hurry?
- Hunting accident. Jack and Twombley.

396
00:32:04,693 --> 00:32:08,356
我以为你知道了　汤比利那快去看看
- I figured you would've heard.
- Twombley! Jesus! Get moving.

397
00:32:08,430 --> 00:32:11,558
我要到那去　我鬼知道...有人搬东西吗
I gotta get up there. How would I have
heard? Have somebody move the grader.

398
00:32:13,702 --> 00:32:19,231
来　你开车
Go on. Go on! You drive.
We'll take my truck.

399
00:32:23,512 --> 00:32:25,412
关了
Turn it off.

400
00:32:25,480 --> 00:32:28,381
你只听说了这些吗
All you heard was there was
some kind of accident?

401
00:32:28,450 --> 00:32:30,577
我听说是汤比利中枪了
Twombley's shot. I heard that.

402
00:32:30,652 --> 00:32:32,677
杰克没事　一定会没事的
Jack's okay, I assume.

403
00:32:32,754 --> 00:32:35,621
你不知道这事有多严重　你是说汤比利？
- You don't know how bad or anything?
- You mean Twombley?

404
00:32:35,691 --> 00:32:38,251
对　就是他
Yes, Wade.
I mean Twombley.

405
00:32:38,327 --> 00:32:40,591
不要再抽烟了
Put out that cigarette!

406
00:32:40,662 --> 00:32:42,721
靠...
Fuck, fuck, fuck!

407
00:32:42,798 --> 00:32:45,665
可能只是打中脚　
Probably shot himself
in the foot or somethin'.

408
00:32:45,734 --> 00:32:47,668
这经常发生的
That's what usually happens.

409
00:32:47,736 --> 00:32:50,967
我本想叫你去陪杰克的　不过现在迟了
- I should've sent you instead of Jack.
- I wish you had.

410
00:32:51,039 --> 00:32:54,668
我可不想自己在冰雪中被冻死掉
I'd rather be deer huntin' than freezin'
my ass off on that fuckin' grader.

411
00:32:54,743 --> 00:32:58,372
但你可是经验老道的警察　
Well, you ain't the hunter Jack is, and
he can't drive the grader worth shit.

412

00:32:58,447 --> 00:33:00,847
像地狱一样
ike hell!

413
00:33:02,684 --> 00:33:07,587
那一定是汤比利　要我跟上去吗
- That must've been Twombley.
- Want me to follow them to Littleton?

414
00:33:07,656 --> 00:33:11,922
不用　我们先上去看看再说
No, no, let's go to the top.
Talk to Jack first.

415
00:33:11,994 --> 00:33:15,430
杰克一定知道这他妈的发生了什么事
He'll know what happened.
He best fucking better know!

416
00:33:24,106 --> 00:33:26,131
那是杰克
There's Jack.

417
00:33:27,542 --> 00:33:29,567
呼叫105频道
I clocked 105.

418
00:33:29,645 --> 00:33:32,375
105？这倒挺快的
105? That was pretty fast.

419
00:33:32,447 --> 00:33:37,384
就像过周末的人一样
Turns out to be
one of these kids up for the weekend.

420
00:33:37,452 --> 00:33:42,253
他说长官　我不想看见这　给我一百块吧
She says, "Officer, can we make this
disappear?" Shows me $100 bill.

421
00:33:42,324 --> 00:33:45,225
收到消息了吗？
Heard the news?

422
00:33:45,293 --> 00:33:47,488
我听说汤比利中枪了　嗯是的
- I heard Twombley got shot.
- Yeah.

423
00:33:47,562 --> 00:33:49,655
小心那狗　韦德
Watch the dog, Wade.

424
00:33:49,731 --> 00:33:52,666
不然它会咬掉你的脑袋　它就像我一样
- Takes a mind to,
he'll take your head off.
- He likes me.

425
00:33:52,734 --> 00:33:55,760
什么情况？30到30的范围之内
- Is it bad?
- 30-30 at close range.

426
00:33:55,837 --> 00:33:57,327
天啊
Jesus!

427
00:33:57,406 --> 00:34:01,035
他怎么了　ＤＯＡ已经把现场封锁了
- Will he make it?
- D.O.A. Blew the bastard wide open.

428
00:34:01,109 --> 00:34:03,134
在汤比利背后有个大洞
Had a hole in his back
you could put your fist into.

429
00:34:03,211 --> 00:34:05,372
前面也有个洞
Nice hole in front too.

430
00:34:05,447 --> 00:34:08,848
你看过吗？不　只是听说
- Did you see it?
- No. Heard it.

431
00:34:08,917 --> 00:34:12,409
我们相距很近　我在盯着那鹿
We weren't far apart.
I'd spotted this buck.

432
00:34:12,487 --> 00:34:14,819
我又看了看他站的位置
I looked at the bottom
of the cliff where he was standin',

433
00:34:14,890 --> 00:34:17,518
然后情况一下子就坏了
and there the fucker was,
deader than shit!

434
00:34:17,592 --> 00:34:19,890
我马上报了警
I called it right in.

435
00:34:19,961 --> 00:34:22,020
这只有一个疑点
This is gonna be one mess
to clean up.

436
00:34:22,097 --> 00:34:24,622
伤者的侄子和女儿都去度假了
Twombley's son-in-law and daughter
are up for the weekend.

437
00:34:24,700 --> 00:34:28,033
韦德　你看到他们了吗　他们就和我几乎无间擦过
- Didn't you say you'd seen him, Wade?
- Yeah. Damn near ran me over.

438
00:34:28,103 --> 00:34:30,264
你想告诉他们　你认识那老头吗
You want to tell them?
You knew the old man.

439
00:34:30,338 --> 00:34:33,796
我他妈哪还有心情说这个
What the fuck!
My day's already ruined.

440
00:34:33,875 --> 00:34:36,036
把钥匙给我　你可以和杰克回去了
Gimme the keys.
You can go back with Jack.

441
00:34:36,111 --> 00:34:39,740
你还有事要做　这事还没完结的
- You still got plowing to do.
- It ain't finished,
if that's what you mean.

442
00:34:39,815 --> 00:34:44,218
有人针对你了？是啊　是有这种感觉
- Something bugging you?
- Yeah, a few things.

443
00:34:44,286 --> 00:34:46,413
我们就对这感觉有兴趣
Right now we're not interested
in a few things.

444
00:34:46,488 --> 00:34:50,447
你有时间的话你干嘛不帮我做点事
Why don't you do a few things
for me, and then you get bugged
on your own time?

445
00:34:53,662 --> 00:34:57,257
你每天只是无所事事
You might as well take the rest
of the day off. You look fucked up.

446
00:34:57,332 --> 00:34:59,323
你也收了小费了是吧？
You've been paid
for the day anyhow, right?

447
00:34:59,401 --> 00:35:01,995
还没收他一毛钱　小费更没给
Not exactly.
I mean, he never paid me.

448
00:35:02,070 --> 00:35:05,437
不用担心　你会有工资收的
Don't worry.
You'll get your money.

449
00:35:05,507 --> 00:35:07,873
不要和媒体说这事
Don't talk to any newspaper
about this.

450
00:35:07,943 --> 00:35:10,741
汤比利可是有影响力的人
Twombley's
a big deal down in Massachusetts.

451
00:35:10,812 --> 00:35:13,178
你只要跟你的律师说　无可奉告
Just tell them that your lawyer
says you shouldn't comment.

452
00:35:13,248 --> 00:35:15,409
律师？我可不需要律师
Lawyer?
I don't need a lawyer, do I?

453
00:35:15,484 --> 00:35:18,180
不，这只是假设　你照做就行了
No, of course not.
Just say it. That's all.

454
00:35:28,697 --> 00:35:31,359
汤哥伤了哪里　胸口
- Where'd Twombley get shot?
- In the chest.

455
00:35:31,433 --> 00:35:35,631
不，我想知道详细地点　大概一里左右的路边
- No. I mean whereabouts.
- About a half mile in,
along the old lumber road.

456
00:35:35,704 --> 00:35:39,572
在路边啊　你带他支那去找猎？
The old lumber road, huh? That's a
steep climb. You bring him up yourself?

457
00:35:39,641 --> 00:35:42,303
救护人员也跟着去了那里
Ambulance guys lugged him up.

458
00:35:44,012 --> 00:35:46,776
你走开了？是的
- You stayed away?
- Yeah.

459
00:35:48,683 --> 00:35:51,413
你这血迹从哪来的？什么血迹
- Where'd you get that blood?
- What blood?

460
00:35:51,486 --> 00:35:53,647
你衣服上的
On your sleeve.

461
00:35:53,722 --> 00:35:57,453
可能是...我怎么知道啊
Must've... Ahh.
How do I know?

462
00:35:57,526 --> 00:35:59,687
你在干什么？询问我吗？
What are you doing, playing cop?

463
00:35:59,761 --> 00:36:03,595
我只是想弄清楚案发的经过
I gotta make a report to Fish and Game.
I'm just wondering, that's all.

464
00:36:03,665 --> 00:36:07,999
你干了什么？谁知道
- What'd he do?
- Who the fuck knows?

465
00:36:08,069 --> 00:36:10,867
一定是滑倒了
Must've slipped or something.

466
00:36:10,939 --> 00:36:13,499
我只是听到枪响的声音
I just heard the gun go off.

467
00:36:14,576 --> 00:36:17,204
我从来没听过有人中枪的
I've never seen a man get shot before.

468
00:36:17,279 --> 00:36:21,113
甚至是在服兵役的时候　一定有什么事情
Not even in the service.
Must be somethin'.

469
00:36:22,751 --> 00:36:26,312
我真的没有看到　真的？
- I didn't actually see it. Like I said.
- Sure you did.

470
00:36:26,388 --> 00:36:28,913
什么？看到他被枪击了
- What?
- Saw him get shot.

471
00:36:28,990 --> 00:36:32,585
你想跟我说什么？我没有看到他被枪击我已经说过了
What the fuck are you telling me?
I never seen the guy get shot.

472
00:36:32,661 --> 00:36:35,596
你一定看到　我知道的
You must've seen him get shot!
I know you did!

473
00:36:37,332 --> 00:36:41,268
你他妈的好烦啊　走开吧别再说这风凉话
Let's get the fuck outta here.
You're not making any sense.

474
00:36:43,805 --> 00:36:47,366
多谢你给我的线索
There's your old 20-gauge, and that's
that new Browning you were showing me.

475
00:36:47,442 --> 00:36:49,842
噢　看这个
Oh, look at this.

476
00:36:49,911 --> 00:36:52,379
这肯定是汤哥的枪吧
That must be Twombley's gun.

477
00:36:52,447 --> 00:36:55,211
最新型号而且制作精良
It's brand-new.
Very fancy tooling, huh?

478
00:36:55,283 --> 00:36:57,376
可能只开过一次火
Probably only been fired one time.

479
00:36:57,452 --> 00:37:02,822
但鬼知道以后还会有什么事　杰克你说是吧
But what the hell, Jack? I guess you
deserve it. Right's right, huh?

480
00:37:02,891 --> 00:37:05,792
汤哥也不会再开枪了
Twombley sure as hell
won't be shooting it again.

